♪ High! ♪

242
00:12:30.624 --> 00:12:33.169
♪ I feel it comin' together ♪

243
00:12:34.295 --> 00:12:36.464
♪ People will see me and cry ♪

244
00:12:36.547 --> 00:12:38.924
Did I ever think I'd be here
on this big lot.

245
00:12:39.008 --> 00:12:42.052
a producer. a director. a star.

246
00:12:42.136 --> 00:12:44.764
a choreographer. a mother?

247
00:12:44.847 --> 00:12:45.681
Absolutely!

248
00:12:45.765 --> 00:12:48.851
♪ Fame! I'm gonna live forever ♪

249
00:12:48.934 --> 00:12:50.186
[music fades and stops]

250
00:12:51.937 --> 00:12:54.690
[Karen]
The pieces that involve more students.

251
00:12:54.774 --> 00:12:58.402
we start with those pieces first.
and we only rehearse on the weekends.

252
00:12:58.486 --> 00:13:01.238
[Debbie] All right. let's go
right at the top of "Toyland."

253
00:13:01.322 --> 00:13:02.823
Enjoy coming alive.

254
00:13:04.325 --> 00:13:05.993
Dolls. little dolls.

255
00:13:06.076 --> 00:13:07.703
["Toyland" music playing]

256
00:13:33.395 --> 00:13:35.606
[Cathie]
Da. da. da. boom. bop! Okay. okay.

257
00:13:35.689 --> 00:13:37.608
What scene were you guys in?

258
00:13:37.691 --> 00:13:39.568
-"Toyland."
-[Cathie] Come on. now.

259
00:13:39.652 --> 00:13:42.196
And what scene are you guys in now?

260
00:13:42.279 --> 00:13:44.698
-[dancers] Well. everything.
-[Cathie] All of them? Yeah. see!

261
00:13:44.782 --> 00:13:46.951
See. "Toyland" is a stepping stone.

262
00:13:47.034 --> 00:13:50.704
Everybody who's everybody
comes through "Toyland."

263
00:13:50.788 --> 00:13:52.456
You are in "Toyland."

264
00:13:52.540 --> 00:13:54.667
I've never even seen a regular Nutcracker.

265
00:13:55.459 --> 00:13:57.461
The only thing I know is Hot Chocolate.

266
00:13:58.796 --> 00:14:00.422
And I-- I kind of like that.

267
00:14:00.923 --> 00:14:02.091
Kylie Jefferson.

268
00:14:02.758 --> 00:14:05.678
She's the youngest person
that I ever put in the Academy.

269
00:14:05.761 --> 00:14:08.389
I remember we walked into…

270
00:14:08.973 --> 00:14:11.016
the Debbie Allen Dance Academy.

271
00:14:11.100 --> 00:14:12.935
in Culver City at the time.

272
00:14:13.018 --> 00:14:16.313
and there were so many people there.

273
00:14:17.523 --> 00:14:20.234
And when we got to the table.
I remember them telling my mom

274
00:14:20.317 --> 00:14:21.902
that I could not audition.

275
00:14:21.986 --> 00:14:23.445
They were like. "She is too young."

276
00:14:23.529 --> 00:14:26.824
She came in in first position.
hair pulled back… [inhales]

277
00:14:27.491 --> 00:14:29.827
…and just so serious.
I'm like. "Oh. yeah."

278
00:14:30.369 --> 00:14:32.830
And Miss Allen said. "Let her audition."

279
00:14:32.913 --> 00:14:36.625
[Debbie] And they all looked at me
and said. "Miss Allen. she's too young."

280
00:14:36.709 --> 00:14:39.128
and I said. "I can change the rules."

281
00:14:41.714 --> 00:14:42.590
Perfect.

282
00:14:42.673 --> 00:14:45.801
Most of my students come from LA.

283
00:14:45.885 --> 00:14:48.387
from various economic backgrounds.

284
00:14:48.470 --> 00:14:50.806
Some of them live in Beverly Hills.

285
00:14:50.890 --> 00:14:52.725
some of them live in Compton.

286
00:14:53.309 --> 00:14:56.145
and those that are the most serious
about dance.

287
00:14:56.228 --> 00:15:01.692
they come at least five.
maybe six days a week.

288
00:15:02.484 --> 00:15:05.696
and they are required to take
no less than ten. up--

289
00:15:05.779 --> 00:15:08.198
Some of them take 15 classes a week.

290
00:15:08.282 --> 00:15:10.910
She wanted to have a place where.
regardless of what you look like.

291
00:15:10.993 --> 00:15:13.579
if you want to dance. you can come dance.

292
00:15:13.662 --> 00:15:17.416
which speaks to why we have a large group
of people that are on scholarships here.

293
00:15:17.499 --> 00:15:19.293
A lot of our kids can't afford to come.

294
00:15:19.376 --> 00:15:21.545
We find a way to…

295
00:15:22.254 --> 00:15:24.715
get people into the doors
who want to be there.

296
00:15:24.798 --> 00:15:26.383
[Debbie] We go. we go. we go.

297
00:15:26.467 --> 00:15:27.718
We've always been raising money.

298
00:15:27.801 --> 00:15:29.595
A lot of my friends
stopped taking my calls

299
00:15:29.678 --> 00:15:31.388
after that first year. [laughs]

300
00:15:31.931 --> 00:15:33.807
But no. my friends have all been so cool.

301
00:15:34.475 --> 00:15:37.311
We started thinking about.
what brand can we use

302
00:15:37.394 --> 00:15:39.480
that's in our toolbox

303
00:15:39.939 --> 00:15:43.943
that can help generate more income.
that would be familiar to people?

304
00:15:44.026 --> 00:15:48.238
When George Balanchine came to New York
to start the New York City Ballet.

305
00:15:48.906 --> 00:15:50.866
he had to find something
that would raise money.

306
00:15:50.950 --> 00:15:53.452
and The Nutcracker was what did it.

307
00:15:53.953 --> 00:15:57.873
It was The Nutcracker
that helped fund the rest of the year

308
00:15:57.957 --> 00:15:59.583
for the New York City Ballet.

309
00:15:59.667 --> 00:16:01.710
[Eartha] The original Nutcracker

310
00:16:01.794 --> 00:16:05.381
is a story told completely--
It's an opera completely in dance.

311
00:16:05.464 --> 00:16:08.258
Our Nutcracker is a narrative.

312
00:16:08.342 --> 00:16:09.843
Hey. Harvey! It's time to go!

313
00:16:09.927 --> 00:16:12.388
The Nutcracker's awake.
We gotta go battle.

314
00:16:12.471 --> 00:16:15.599
[Eartha] We have a narrator. or narrators.

315
00:16:15.683 --> 00:16:17.935
who are taking us through the journey.

316
00:16:18.018 --> 00:16:22.982
and it's more--
It's comedy in here that is spoken.

317
00:16:23.065 --> 00:16:24.525
It's not mimed.

318
00:16:24.608 --> 00:16:26.735
-[glass shatters]
-[screams]

319
00:16:26.819 --> 00:16:28.904
Ooh! Who turned out the lights?

320
00:16:28.988 --> 00:16:31.407
-Who turned out the lights?
-[audience laughs]

321
00:16:31.490 --> 00:16:34.910
It just caught on like wildfire.
It's a huge part of our fundraising.

322
00:16:34.994 --> 00:16:36.870
It's probably
our largest single fundraiser.

323
00:16:37.788 --> 00:16:40.749
[Debbie] This is gonna tell me
who's doing this tilt. Ooh no!

324
00:16:40.833 --> 00:16:42.167
Get the leg up!

325
00:16:42.710 --> 00:16:47.131
You need to sit in that split
while you're watching TV. doing homework.

326
00:16:47.214 --> 00:16:48.632
You all don't do that enough.

327
00:16:48.716 --> 00:16:51.927
You all are too busy talking to boys
and doing other things.

328
00:16:52.011 --> 00:16:55.222
Get the leg up higher.
Come on. I'm gonna get it this time.

329
00:16:55.305 --> 00:16:56.223
Up!

330
00:16:57.141 --> 00:16:58.100
Up!

331
00:16:58.183 --> 00:16:59.601
Tilt over! Bend!

332
00:16:59.685 --> 00:17:01.186
Yes. bend!

333
00:17:01.270 --> 00:17:04.398
Yes. hold yourself and get the leg up!

334
00:17:04.481 --> 00:17:05.315
That!

335
00:17:06.191 --> 00:17:09.403
Well. my first memory of DADA
would be when I was 11.

336
00:17:10.988 --> 00:17:14.700
I was so scared
'cause I didn't even know.

337
00:17:14.783 --> 00:17:17.327
like. people could be this. like. good.

338
00:17:17.411 --> 00:17:19.872
'Cause I was. like 11.
and I was. like. "I'm the best."

339
00:17:19.955 --> 00:17:21.165
Then I was like. "Nope."

340
00:17:23.542 --> 00:17:27.296
The teachers here. they're hard on you.
and they're tough. but they care.

341
00:17:28.630 --> 00:17:30.758
I just feel like it's a family.

342
00:17:30.841 --> 00:17:33.302
Miss Allen cares
about every single one of us.

343
00:17:33.385 --> 00:17:35.596
which is. like. really good.

344
00:17:39.600 --> 00:17:41.852
[girl] I've been at DADA for nine years.

345
00:17:41.935 --> 00:17:44.313
since I was five. and I'm 14 now.

346
00:17:44.396 --> 00:17:48.400
So… I've basically grown up in DADA.

347
00:17:51.361 --> 00:17:53.572
When they first told me I was Kara.

348
00:17:53.655 --> 00:17:56.658
I was. like. nervous and happy

349
00:17:56.742 --> 00:18:00.162
because I felt like I had
such a big responsibility

350
00:18:00.245 --> 00:18:04.166
to. like. make sure I wouldn't mess up
or. like. screw up the entire show.

351
00:18:04.249 --> 00:18:06.001
Everybody wants to be Kara.

352
00:18:06.085 --> 00:18:08.212
which is the lead role.

353
00:18:08.295 --> 00:18:11.173
She's the little girl
who goes on an adventure.

354
00:18:11.757 --> 00:18:14.343
And Miss Allen
always double casts the show

355
00:18:14.426 --> 00:18:17.221
so that people
get to interchange their roles

356
00:18:17.304 --> 00:18:19.640
and have different experiences.

357
00:18:19.723 --> 00:18:20.849
[photographer] Nice.

358
00:18:20.933 --> 00:18:23.811
-♪ Kara. Kara. won't you smile? ♪
-To the camera.

359
00:18:23.894 --> 00:18:27.022
-♪ Take a look. tell me what you think ♪
-Tell me what you think!

360
00:18:27.106 --> 00:18:31.902
I remember Miss Allen. she told me
that I was gonna be Kara for three shows.

361
00:18:32.820 --> 00:18:34.488
and I literally freaked out.

362
00:18:34.571 --> 00:18:36.573
♪ My dear. such a surprise ♪

363
00:18:36.657 --> 00:18:39.535
♪ Surprise
Surprise. surprise. surprise! ♪

364
00:18:39.618 --> 00:18:42.663
-[all] ♪ Kara. Kara ♪
-Kara!

365
00:18:42.746 --> 00:18:44.498
♪ Kara. Kara ♪

366
00:18:44.581 --> 00:18:46.458
[girl] You know we love you!

367
00:18:46.542 --> 00:18:49.419
It's that feeling when it's like
you have a goal. and you reach it.

368
00:18:49.503 --> 00:18:53.549
and you meet it. and it's like. "Yes!"
You know? So I was so happy.

369
00:18:53.632 --> 00:18:55.008
[indistinct chattering]

370
00:18:58.137 --> 00:19:01.348
[Debbie]
Now. let's talk about the Egyptian Doll.

371
00:19:02.099 --> 00:19:07.020
You wanna get right under her little butt.
and you have her hand. if she needs it.

372
00:19:07.104 --> 00:19:09.022
And you press her all the way up.

373
00:19:09.773 --> 00:19:12.860
That is the position.
and you're on the other side.

374
00:19:12.943 --> 00:19:16.655
I was the first Egyptian Doll.
My mother choreographed that on me.

375
00:19:17.156 --> 00:19:18.490
[solemn music playing]

376
00:19:20.242 --> 00:19:21.076
Boo!

377
00:19:21.535 --> 00:19:23.036
And one and two.

378
00:19:23.120 --> 00:19:25.038
One. two. three.

379
00:19:25.122 --> 00:19:27.875
Single turn. open. Head. head.

380
00:19:28.458 --> 00:19:32.754
[Vivian] I really started training
heavily and seriously in dance

381
00:19:32.838 --> 00:19:34.173
at the Kirov Academy of Ballet.

382
00:19:34.256 --> 00:19:37.634
It's about right here
that you start. She splits.

383
00:19:38.135 --> 00:19:39.887
[Vivian] My third year there.

384
00:19:39.970 --> 00:19:43.182
my teacher looked at me one day in class.

385
00:19:43.265 --> 00:19:45.517
and goes. "Stop. stop. stop. stop. stop!"

386
00:19:46.852 --> 00:19:48.979
And. um.
he looked at me. and he goes.

387
00:19:49.062 --> 00:19:50.647
[in Russian accent]
"You never be dancer.

388
00:19:51.148 --> 00:19:52.524
You go Alvin Ailey."

389
00:19:52.608 --> 00:19:54.193
And that was a dig.

390
00:19:54.693 --> 00:19:57.112
[Debbie] Like Alvin Ailey was nothing?

391
00:19:57.196 --> 00:19:59.072
[chuckles] Alvin Ailey's our premier.

392
00:19:59.573 --> 00:20:02.201
you know.
contemporary American dance company.

393
00:20:02.826 --> 00:20:05.204
and. yes. it's mostly Black people. but…

394
00:20:06.371 --> 00:20:08.081
that means she can't dance?

395
00:20:08.582 --> 00:20:11.543
Child. I was coming through that phone.
I was getting ready--

396
00:20:11.627 --> 00:20:14.922
I sent my husband
because I knew I was not gonna be nice.

397
00:20:15.005 --> 00:20:18.842
For me. having my daughter gone
for a coup-- three or four-- three years.

398
00:20:18.926 --> 00:20:21.053
it was time for her to come back home
in my eyes anyway.

399
00:20:21.136 --> 00:20:22.763
He pulled me out of the school.

400
00:20:23.305 --> 00:20:26.058
and that's when my mother decided

401
00:20:26.141 --> 00:20:28.518
that she was gonna create
the Debbie Allen Dance Academy.

402
00:20:28.602 --> 00:20:32.439
And so I started DADA. and she came home.

403
00:20:32.522 --> 00:20:33.982
She was the inspiration.

404
00:20:34.066 --> 00:20:36.235
She's my muse. She always has been.

405
00:20:37.611 --> 00:20:39.863
[Karen]
There's something here for everyone.

406
00:20:39.947 --> 00:20:44.826
You know. every shape.
every size. every color. every culture.

407
00:20:44.910 --> 00:20:46.787
and that makes us very unique.

408
00:20:47.287 --> 00:20:51.041
And she's gonna walk over.
and then you all recede back.

409
00:20:51.124 --> 00:20:52.209
She is the one.

410
00:20:53.377 --> 00:20:55.420
-She's adorable.
-And she's fierce.

411
00:20:55.504 --> 00:20:57.297
-She's fierce.
-[instructor laughs]

412
00:21:01.218 --> 00:21:03.011
[Debbie]
April is cutting where she has to cut.

413
00:21:03.095 --> 00:21:05.555
You all need to keep coming around.
You can do it.

414
00:21:06.974 --> 00:21:10.727
[April] I didn't start actually dancing
until I was eight years old.

415
00:21:11.520 --> 00:21:13.397
I came here from North Carolina.

416
00:21:13.480 --> 00:21:17.609
and I-- I received full scholarship
by Debbie Allen.

417
00:21:17.693 --> 00:21:24.199
April is one of the most gifted dancers
I've ever come into my circle.

418
00:21:24.866 --> 00:21:27.411
And I brought her here
so we could nurture her

419
00:21:27.494 --> 00:21:28.620
because she needs it.

420
00:21:28.704 --> 00:21:31.707
[April]
I have a part-time job at El Pollo Loco.

421
00:21:31.790 --> 00:21:32.791
I'm a cashier.

422
00:21:33.458 --> 00:21:36.128
So. right now. I'm a cashier.

423
00:21:40.966 --> 00:21:43.844
People usually see me as a quiet person.

424
00:21:43.927 --> 00:21:45.637
and. like. most of the time.

425
00:21:45.721 --> 00:21:48.432
I have a lot to say.
or I have a lot on my mind.

426
00:21:48.515 --> 00:21:52.936
but I just don't know how to…
you know. I don't know how to say it.

427
00:21:53.020 --> 00:21:57.316
And sometimes. like.
I have so much emotions inside of myself.

428
00:21:58.358 --> 00:22:03.488
and the only way I can get my emotions
or my fear or my anxiety out

429
00:22:03.572 --> 00:22:05.157
is through dance.

430
00:22:10.078 --> 00:22:11.163
[Giana] Ready?

431
00:22:11.246 --> 00:22:12.956
[Bollywood music playing]

432
00:22:13.040 --> 00:22:13.874
[Debbie] Breathe!

433
00:22:14.791 --> 00:22:15.667
Beautiful!

434
00:22:16.918 --> 00:22:17.753
Beautiful.

435
00:22:18.420 --> 00:22:20.964
You're the most beautiful people
on the planet.

436
00:22:21.882 --> 00:22:23.800
[Cathie]
Once again. it's about the mirror.

437
00:22:27.679 --> 00:22:30.599
[Debbie]
The most beautiful beings on this Earth.

438
00:22:31.475 --> 00:22:32.434
[shouts] Bop!

439
00:22:33.727 --> 00:22:34.561
Bop.

440
00:22:35.645 --> 00:22:36.480
Bop.

441
00:22:37.397 --> 00:22:39.983
-And one.
-[Cathie] The head. one person moving.

442
00:22:40.067 --> 00:22:41.485
The whole rhythm.

443
00:22:41.568 --> 00:22:45.405
this whole thing has to feel like
one person moving.

444
00:22:46.531 --> 00:22:47.407
[Debbie] Look up!

445
00:22:51.703 --> 00:22:52.537
Down.

446
00:22:55.540 --> 00:22:57.626
[Jalyn] I wanna be in "Bollywood" so bad.

447
00:22:57.709 --> 00:23:00.545
I've been trying to get in "Bollywood"
for the longest.

448
00:23:00.629 --> 00:23:04.674
I know every step. but. you know.
I'm too young to be in "Bollywood."

449
00:23:04.758 --> 00:23:05.592
[Debbie] Upper body!

450
00:23:05.675 --> 00:23:07.427
[Karen]
When we go to a different country.

451
00:23:07.511 --> 00:23:10.389
that allows
for new choreography. new costumes.

452
00:23:10.472 --> 00:23:12.599
It allows for a new part of the story.

453
00:23:13.183 --> 00:23:14.017
[Debbie] Back.

454
00:23:14.601 --> 00:23:15.435
Travel.

455
00:23:19.147 --> 00:23:20.148
Wherever you go.

456
00:23:20.232 --> 00:23:25.195
you have an aura of superiority
and beauty and power.

457
00:23:25.278 --> 00:23:26.154
Power!

458
00:23:26.238 --> 00:23:28.031
This is about women's power.

459
00:23:28.115 --> 00:23:30.575
Women rule the world!
I don't care what they say.

460
00:23:32.828 --> 00:23:33.662
Voom!

461
00:23:34.287 --> 00:23:35.664
Bop. Where am I?

462
00:23:35.747 --> 00:23:36.581
Ta. ta. ta!

463
00:23:37.499 --> 00:23:38.375
Ta. ta!

464
00:23:38.458 --> 00:23:40.168
It's in the eyes. all of it.

465
00:23:42.045 --> 00:23:44.548
"Bollywood."
you would think it would be my favorite.

466
00:23:44.631 --> 00:23:45.632
it's everybody's favorite.

467
00:23:45.715 --> 00:23:48.552
It's something you. like.
dream about being in until you're in it.

468
00:23:48.635 --> 00:23:51.763
It's five minutes
of straight full-out dancing.

469
00:23:51.847 --> 00:23:53.265
and there's no time to breathe.

470
00:23:54.683 --> 00:23:56.309
[Debbie in background] One. One.

471
00:24:01.481 --> 00:24:04.443
-[Cathie clapping rhythm]
-[Debbie] And jump! Power!

472
00:24:04.526 --> 00:24:06.111
[vocalizing]

473
00:24:06.194 --> 00:24:07.779
Power! Bop!

474
00:24:12.868 --> 00:24:13.827
[music stops]

475
00:24:13.910 --> 00:24:15.495
[Debbie] And stay forever.

476
00:24:15.579 --> 00:24:18.123
Stay. Stay there. Breathe. Stay.

477
00:24:18.707 --> 00:24:20.000
Practice holding it.

478
00:24:20.083 --> 00:24:21.209
It's good for you.

479
00:24:23.170 --> 00:24:24.963
It's getting better. ladies.

480
00:24:25.964 --> 00:24:27.799
Okay. break. Getting better.

481
00:24:27.883 --> 00:24:28.925
Listen to me.

482
00:24:29.009 --> 00:24:32.721
You're going much wider than you need to.
You're killing yourselves.

483
00:24:32.804 --> 00:24:34.514
Okay. breathe.
then we're gonna do "Egypt."

484
00:24:34.598 --> 00:24:36.016
Just breathe. Breathe.

485
00:24:36.516 --> 00:24:37.601
You have two minutes.

486
00:24:40.520 --> 00:24:43.148
Okay. so. Miss Nicholas.

487
00:24:46.109 --> 00:24:48.278
Okay. we're really gonna be okay.

488
00:24:48.361 --> 00:24:50.906
but they're just raggedy.
Too raggedy for me right--

489
00:24:50.989 --> 00:24:54.159
I can't-- uh. '"Fairyland."
I'm-- I'm not feelin' it. No.

490
00:24:54.701 --> 00:24:58.747
So I'm adding. in yellow.
things that we're going to rehearse.

491
00:25:01.333 --> 00:25:04.127
Okay. now. I gotta go terrorize
the fairies. I'm sorry.

492
00:25:04.920 --> 00:25:06.463
[piano playing "Fairyland" music]

493
00:25:11.134 --> 00:25:12.677
Because I came from DADA.

494
00:25:12.761 --> 00:25:17.891
I didn't realize how big of a deal
that I was a Black girl who does ballet.

495
00:25:17.974 --> 00:25:18.892
[Debbie] Lovely!

496
00:25:20.602 --> 00:25:24.898
[Kylie] Like. the world
is so different from DADA. [chuckles]

497
00:25:24.981 --> 00:25:28.652
'Cause. where I come from. we all do it.
and we were all good.

498
00:25:32.113 --> 00:25:33.114
[Debbie] Lauren Anderson.

499
00:25:33.198 --> 00:25:38.328
who was the first Black ballerina
in a major ballet company.

500
00:25:38.411 --> 00:25:40.121
came here a year ago.

501
00:25:40.205 --> 00:25:43.792
And a one. and two.
pas de cheval. enveloppé.

502
00:25:43.875 --> 00:25:47.379
I never thought. "I wanna be
a ballet dancer." not at the age of seven.

503
00:25:48.797 --> 00:25:51.132
I just thought it was fun
taking the classes.

504
00:25:52.592 --> 00:25:56.638
So I just really didn't realize
the impact of being African American

505
00:25:56.721 --> 00:25:57.931
and a principal dancer.

506
00:26:01.142 --> 00:26:06.064
And I found out there weren't very many.
There weren't any at that time. really.

507
00:26:06.147 --> 00:26:09.359
Unless you were in Alvin Ailey
or Dance Theatre of Harlem.

508
00:26:10.819 --> 00:26:13.572
But I just wanted to dance.
That wasn't my big focus.

509
00:26:13.655 --> 00:26:15.365
that I wanted to be
the first Black anything.

510
00:26:15.448 --> 00:26:16.783
I just wanted to dance.

511
00:26:16.866 --> 00:26:18.827
Plié. one. and stretch.

512
00:26:22.956 --> 00:26:24.624
[lively ballet music playing]

513
00:26:26.710 --> 00:26:28.295
[Lauren]
When I first saw April.

514
00:26:28.920 --> 00:26:32.173
I thought. "Wow!
Where did that come from?"

515
00:26:32.257 --> 00:26:34.884
That's somebody
that's born with everything.

516
00:26:39.848 --> 00:26:40.974
[Debbie] Yes!

517
00:26:42.017 --> 00:26:42.851
Love it.

518
00:26:46.146 --> 00:26:49.149
What I need is something that sustains.
I feel like it's…

519
00:26:49.899 --> 00:26:51.192
I want it to be lighter.

520
00:26:51.276 --> 00:26:52.736
[scats softly]

521
00:26:52.819 --> 00:26:56.656
[April] I don't think I ha--
necessarily have a ballet body right now.

522
00:26:56.740 --> 00:26:58.908
as of this moment… [chuckles]

523
00:26:58.992 --> 00:27:02.746
…because my legs
are just a little bit overdeveloped.

524
00:27:02.829 --> 00:27:04.623
[Debbie scats rhythmically]

525
00:27:05.165 --> 00:27:09.127
And when you get really serious. you start
looking at yourself in a certain way.

526
00:27:09.210 --> 00:27:12.422
Chaîné. chaîné. chaîné.
chaîné. chaîné. chaîné. chaîné.

527
00:27:12.505 --> 00:27:13.923
Stop on a dime.

528
00:27:14.883 --> 00:27:15.759
And stay.

529
00:27:16.343 --> 00:27:21.264
But when I'm in the ballet world.
mostly everyone is pretty thin.

530
00:27:21.348 --> 00:27:24.559
In high school.
I really had no problem with it.

531
00:27:24.643 --> 00:27:27.479
and then you realize
that maybe you should look at it.

532
00:27:27.562 --> 00:27:30.732
because everybody else looks
at weight and…

533
00:27:30.815 --> 00:27:34.277
Everything matters.
Everything is so particular in ballet.

534
00:27:34.361 --> 00:27:36.696
She might not have the perfect legs
and feet. I didn't.

535
00:27:36.780 --> 00:27:38.239
Most people don't.

536
00:27:38.323 --> 00:27:41.034
Most people that do ballet
do not have perfect legs and feet.

537
00:27:41.117 --> 00:27:43.536
It's something you've worked for.

538
00:27:43.620 --> 00:27:44.954
Turnout you've worked for.

539
00:27:45.580 --> 00:27:48.208
You don't-- don't just come out going.
"Chick-a-bah."

540
00:27:48.291 --> 00:27:49.334
Some people do.

541
00:27:50.418 --> 00:27:51.961
but most of us don't.

542
00:27:52.921 --> 00:27:54.506
[soothing music playing]

543
00:28:07.185 --> 00:28:10.355
There have been times
where I was so down on myself

544
00:28:10.438 --> 00:28:13.400
about my body and just. like. so. ugh.

545
00:28:13.483 --> 00:28:16.736
like. negative and insecure about it.

546
00:28:20.865 --> 00:28:21.783
But… [exhales]

547
00:28:24.160 --> 00:28:26.204
I had to stop playing the victim…

548
00:28:27.455 --> 00:28:28.623
towards myself.

549
00:28:29.499 --> 00:28:33.378
There was a moment where I realized.
like. "Look. if I wanna do this.

550
00:28:34.045 --> 00:28:36.631
I have to figure out
what's gonna work for me."

551
00:28:39.509 --> 00:28:41.261
But what was hard was understanding

552
00:28:41.344 --> 00:28:45.640
that the craft that chose me
was not created in my image.

553
00:28:45.724 --> 00:28:48.226
and that was a really hard realization.

554
00:28:49.144 --> 00:28:52.272
But. at the same time.
you know. this craft chose me.

555
00:28:52.355 --> 00:28:55.859
I have no choice but to do it
and to give it my all.

556
00:28:55.942 --> 00:28:58.903
-[classical music playing]
-[Debbie speaking indistinctly]

557
00:29:01.364 --> 00:29:03.116
[Debbie] You know. in Russia. they…

558
00:29:03.199 --> 00:29:07.036
x-ray the children's feet
and their backs and their bodies

559
00:29:07.120 --> 00:29:08.413
before they even accept them.

560
00:29:09.038 --> 00:29:11.791
Well. I mean. that's the world of ballet.

561
00:29:11.875 --> 00:29:13.293
[dramatic music playing]

562
00:29:17.630 --> 00:29:22.010
In a opera. uh. they will select
only children who have voice.

563
00:29:24.888 --> 00:29:27.348
They cannot make a voice. It is gift.

564
00:29:27.432 --> 00:29:29.642
Same things with a ballet facility.

565
00:29:29.726 --> 00:29:33.271
They have to have certain physiques
for that.

566
00:29:34.439 --> 00:29:35.732
You cannot make it.

567
00:29:37.817 --> 00:29:40.904
The Kirov
and the Russian method is important.

568
00:29:40.987 --> 00:29:44.240
It is the technique
that I love the best to teach.

569
00:29:45.241 --> 00:29:48.620
And that's why we have Madame Giana
who's from the Bolshoi.

570
00:29:48.703 --> 00:29:51.664
But the dance world is evolving.

571
00:29:51.748 --> 00:29:56.544
so I'm reinventing a bit.
for the teachers.

572
00:29:57.378 --> 00:30:00.256
what their mission is
and how they go about it.

573
00:30:00.965 --> 00:30:02.550
I want the spirit of the dance.

574
00:30:02.634 --> 00:30:05.303
That's not something
you can take a picture of.

575
00:30:05.386 --> 00:30:07.764
That's something you feel and you see.

576
00:30:07.847 --> 00:30:09.098
You experience.

577
00:30:09.182 --> 00:30:10.975
One. two. Not bad.

578
00:30:11.059 --> 00:30:13.853
One. two. One. two.

579
00:30:13.937 --> 00:30:16.314
Okay. not that bad. Go back.

580
00:30:16.981 --> 00:30:18.233
It actually helped.

581
00:30:18.983 --> 00:30:20.068
It looked better.

582
00:30:20.151 --> 00:30:22.737
I'm sorry. Madame Giana.
it looked better.

583
00:30:22.821 --> 00:30:24.030
No. no. I disagree.

584
00:30:24.113 --> 00:30:26.074
-Because they look like this.
-I disagree.

585
00:30:26.157 --> 00:30:27.951
-It's okay. It's all right.
-It's "Oh!

586
00:30:28.034 --> 00:30:29.452
-[dancers laugh]
-Oh!"

587
00:30:29.536 --> 00:30:32.163
It's all right. Five. six.

588
00:30:32.247 --> 00:30:35.583
They're just practicing.
Six. seven. eight.

589
00:30:35.667 --> 00:30:38.920
And one. and two. and one. and two.

590
00:30:39.003 --> 00:30:40.547
and one. and two.

591
00:30:40.630 --> 00:30:44.008
Some of you. uh. don't have the timing.
and you're a little stiff.

592
00:30:44.592 --> 00:30:45.969
You know. you've gotta relax.

593
00:30:46.052 --> 00:30:48.805
I'm sorry. but I have to just say
what I'm seeing right now

594
00:30:48.888 --> 00:30:51.099
because. um. we don't have a lot of time.

595
00:30:51.182 --> 00:30:54.143
And either they're doing it right
right now. or they're not.

596
00:30:54.227 --> 00:30:56.563
Even though we're gonna clean it.
I know that.

597
00:30:56.646 --> 00:30:59.399
But I know. technically.
if somebody's going like this.

598
00:30:59.482 --> 00:31:01.401
that's not gonna change tomorrow.

599
00:31:01.484 --> 00:31:02.652
Go back. ladies.

600
00:31:04.028 --> 00:31:06.781
Five. six. seven. and eight.

601
00:31:06.865 --> 00:31:10.034
And one. and two. and one. and two.

602
00:31:10.118 --> 00:31:13.162
and one. and two. and one. and two.

603
00:31:13.246 --> 00:31:14.205
Much better!

604
00:31:14.289 --> 00:31:16.207
And two. and one. and two.

605
00:31:16.291 --> 00:31:18.793
Much better! Much better!

606
00:31:18.877 --> 00:31:20.628
Sorry. Madame Giana. it's better.

607
00:31:20.712 --> 00:31:22.380
Okay. go back to the beginning.

608
00:31:23.339 --> 00:31:25.592
It's better. You know it is.

609
00:31:25.675 --> 00:31:27.343
[classical musical playing]

610
00:31:35.643 --> 00:31:42.609
[Debbie] The teachers are so vested
and so dedicated to these young people.

611
00:31:43.276 --> 00:31:45.486
They go home with them.
They give them food.

612
00:31:45.570 --> 00:31:48.781
They'll scold them
if they need to pull them together.

613
00:31:49.365 --> 00:31:50.533
You know. we go in.

614
00:31:50.617 --> 00:31:53.453
We're raising--
we're helping to raise these kids.

615
00:32:18.144 --> 00:32:21.064
I grew up in Houston. Texas.
Everything was segregated.

616
00:32:21.147 --> 00:32:24.442
You know. white water fountain only.

617
00:32:25.026 --> 00:32:27.403
colored bathroom…
We had experienced all that.

618
00:32:28.029 --> 00:32:29.489
There was a great dance school.

619
00:32:29.572 --> 00:32:31.991
but I was not allowed to go
because I was Black.

620
00:32:33.326 --> 00:32:36.746
But I was very serious early on.
I knew I really wanted it and…

621
00:32:37.246 --> 00:32:40.875
My mom always says
that. when I was eight years old.

622
00:32:40.959 --> 00:32:43.711
I said to her.
"Mom. I'm trying to be a dancer.

623
00:32:43.795 --> 00:32:45.838
How am I gonna get there
if I don't have lessons?

624
00:32:45.922 --> 00:32:48.091
I need real lessons. Mom.

625
00:32:48.174 --> 00:32:49.592
Real lessons."

626
00:32:52.011 --> 00:32:53.888
At 14 years old.

627
00:32:53.972 --> 00:32:57.183
I was recruited
by Madame Tatiana Semenova.

628
00:32:57.892 --> 00:32:59.978
who came from the Mariinsky school.

629
00:33:00.603 --> 00:33:04.190
I was so excited. I had to get up.
I had to go way across town.

630
00:33:04.273 --> 00:33:07.860
My Uncle Lloyd would take me.
and I-- if I had to take a bus back.

631
00:33:07.944 --> 00:33:10.154
it was two or three buses
to get back home.

632
00:33:11.364 --> 00:33:15.118
And. uh. Madame Semenova
really embraced me in class.

633
00:33:15.201 --> 00:33:19.455
It was a Ford Foundation grant
that paid for all of my classes.

634
00:33:19.539 --> 00:33:21.290
I was a full scholarship student.

635
00:33:22.041 --> 00:33:23.543
And when I danced.

636
00:33:24.419 --> 00:33:27.839
it was a big deal because the board
didn't know that I was there.

637
00:33:27.922 --> 00:33:31.759
I was there probably six or eight months

638
00:33:32.260 --> 00:33:35.596
before the board knew
there was a Black kid in the school.

639
00:33:35.680 --> 00:33:38.516
and some of them did not like it.

640
00:33:39.475 --> 00:33:42.061
But Madame Semenova pushed me.

641
00:33:42.145 --> 00:33:44.731
she scolded me. she humiliated me.

642
00:33:45.481 --> 00:33:46.524
and she loved me.

643
00:33:52.155 --> 00:33:53.531
[classical music playing]

644
00:33:54.657 --> 00:33:58.119
All right.
welcome to "the hell that is Chantel."

645
00:33:58.202 --> 00:34:00.079
-Here we go. so…
-[kids laughing]

646
00:34:00.163 --> 00:34:01.748
I grew up as a foster kid.

647
00:34:01.831 --> 00:34:04.709
This is the one thing
that saves somebody like me.

648
00:34:04.792 --> 00:34:07.462
For somebody else to see and invest in me

649
00:34:07.545 --> 00:34:11.174
and say. "We see what it is that you want.

650
00:34:11.257 --> 00:34:14.260
We're gonna help you do this
and get you from point A to point B."

651
00:34:14.343 --> 00:34:18.431
I feel like that. in itself.
is the biggest thing that changed my life.

652
00:34:20.016 --> 00:34:21.684
Boom. boom. Sit. sit. Boom. up!

653
00:34:22.977 --> 00:34:23.895
Where you at?

654
00:34:24.562 --> 00:34:25.688
I don't know.

655
00:34:25.772 --> 00:34:28.107
If you do this bang again.
I'm about to be…

656
00:34:28.191 --> 00:34:31.652
Elijah. go get me. um.
go get me a little rubber band. please?

657
00:34:31.736 --> 00:34:33.613
[chattering]

658
00:34:33.696 --> 00:34:35.156
[Elijah] Looks so cute. though.

659
00:34:35.239 --> 00:34:38.117
[chuckles] Shut up.
Shut up. Elijah. Five…

660
00:34:38.659 --> 00:34:41.496
Five. six. seven. cross.

661
00:34:41.579 --> 00:34:43.247
Cross and sit. sit.

662
00:34:43.331 --> 00:34:46.584
-I was an understudy. but I came--
-Yeah. Griffin…

663
00:34:46.667 --> 00:34:48.920
Miss Chantel said
I could be in "Candy Cane." so…

664
00:34:49.003 --> 00:34:52.840
Yeah. he was first an understudy.
but then he started trying to dance.

665
00:34:52.924 --> 00:34:57.720
He's tr-- trying really. really hard.
and then he ended up being in the show.

666
00:34:57.804 --> 00:35:02.433
"Candy Cane" is fun. It's hip-hop. so…
you just hype and fun and full out and…

667
00:35:02.517 --> 00:35:04.060
Yeah. "Candy Cane" is really fun.

668
00:35:04.143 --> 00:35:06.312
"Candy Cane." it's an all-boys scene.

669
00:35:06.854 --> 00:35:10.358
and it's hip-hop. and hip-hop's
one of my favorite styles. so…

670
00:35:10.858 --> 00:35:13.486
Unfortunately. I can't be in it.
but it's my favorite scene.

671
00:35:13.569 --> 00:35:16.447
"Candy Cane" is for the boys.
"Fairyland" is the girls.

672
00:35:16.531 --> 00:35:17.573
You gotta have the--

673
00:35:17.657 --> 00:35:20.785
You know. DADA has always had
more boys than any school.

674
00:35:20.868 --> 00:35:23.496
It's because I'm pushing them
and I want them.

675
00:35:23.579 --> 00:35:26.124
And I have to--
I have to have something to give them.

676
00:35:26.207 --> 00:35:28.292
[Chantel] Olivia. go in the center.

677
00:35:31.379 --> 00:35:32.755
Scoot back. back up.

678
00:35:32.839 --> 00:35:35.341
[female dancer]
My favorite scene would be "Candy Cane."

679
00:35:35.424 --> 00:35:37.218
It's. like. the only hip-hop in the show.

680
00:35:37.301 --> 00:35:38.761
It's all boys.

681
00:35:38.845 --> 00:35:41.639
Six. five. behind him.

682
00:35:41.722 --> 00:35:44.809
Are you going to put the girls in?
Going to put the girls in?

683
00:35:44.892 --> 00:35:45.935
Yeah. I'm doing that.

684
00:35:46.018 --> 00:35:48.646
-I'm gonna get in trouble. but whatever.
-[chuckles] Okay.

685
00:35:48.729 --> 00:35:51.190
Da. da. da. Cross. cross. up. down.

686
00:35:51.274 --> 00:35:52.316
So I need-- Yes!

687
00:35:52.400 --> 00:35:55.653
I need to see cross. up…
That's almost like a élevé.

688
00:35:55.736 --> 00:36:00.158
Over my dead body.
No girls in "Candy Cane." [laughs]

689
00:36:00.241 --> 00:36:03.327
-Yeah. that's not happening. No girls.
-It got around.

690
00:36:03.411 --> 00:36:05.997
It almost happened. though.
but. you know. it's okay.

691
00:36:06.080 --> 00:36:08.332
-I'm in everything else. so…
-[laughs]

692
00:36:08.416 --> 00:36:11.961
Sorry. girls. You know.
it's only us. you know. [giggles]

693
00:36:12.044 --> 00:36:13.671
-[hip-hop music playing]
-[Debbie] Yeah.

694
00:36:14.881 --> 00:36:16.174
Wow!

695
00:36:16.924 --> 00:36:18.092
Wow!

696
00:36:22.930 --> 00:36:25.892
[man] Oh. it's definitely muscle memory.
When you have Chantel Heath

697
00:36:25.975 --> 00:36:28.519
taking you to the depths
of. like. yourself.

698
00:36:28.603 --> 00:36:30.062
you won't forget it too much.

699
00:36:30.146 --> 00:36:32.273
[laughs. vocalizes]

700
00:36:32.356 --> 00:36:33.482
Now run! [laughs]

701
00:36:33.566 --> 00:36:36.444
And one. and two. down. bring it up.

702
00:36:36.527 --> 00:36:37.570
Yeah.

703
00:36:37.653 --> 00:36:41.616
Slide. one. two. Yup. it's--
The whole thing is still there.

704
00:36:41.699 --> 00:36:45.578
[dancers chant]
Who are we? Candy Cane!

705
00:36:45.661 --> 00:36:48.873
[Chantel vocalizing rhythm]

706
00:36:48.956 --> 00:36:52.543
Throw! [vocalizing rhythm]

707
00:36:52.627 --> 00:36:54.003
Turn. and one.

708
00:36:54.837 --> 00:36:56.088
It's no joke. huh?

709
00:36:57.298 --> 00:37:00.468
Some boys fall apart.
Some boys don't make it. I mean…

710
00:37:01.052 --> 00:37:03.721
You know. they're like. "Oh. my God.
That was hard. that was hard."

711
00:37:03.804 --> 00:37:05.097
I know. sit down.

712
00:37:05.181 --> 00:37:06.265
Just a second.

713
00:37:06.349 --> 00:37:09.393
What I know is. if I was doing it. I'd be…

714
00:37:09.477 --> 00:37:11.854
still dancing right now
'cause the song would still be on.

715
00:37:11.938 --> 00:37:13.648
Let's get it. All right. show's on!
Let's go!

716
00:37:13.731 --> 00:37:15.733
But I tell them.
"Keep coming back. keep coming back.

717
00:37:15.816 --> 00:37:17.652
because one of these days.
you're gonna get it."

718
00:37:17.735 --> 00:37:19.528
I don't know if everyone sticks with it.

719
00:37:19.612 --> 00:37:24.951
but I know for a fact that. if you
are here longer than a-- a semester.

720
00:37:25.034 --> 00:37:27.745
me. personally. that it's inside you.

721
00:37:27.828 --> 00:37:29.497
[Chantel]
Boom. boom. sit. sit! Boom. boom…

