[Debbie] Welcome. you all.
to the Hot Chocolate Nutcracker.

1235
01:04:28.489 --> 01:04:30.324
[audience cheering. applauding]

1236
01:04:33.411 --> 01:04:36.080
My name is Debbie Allen.
and I'm here to…

1237
01:04:36.163 --> 01:04:37.415
[audience cheering]

1238
01:04:39.333 --> 01:04:40.293
[Debbie] Thank you.

1239
01:04:40.835 --> 01:04:43.921
When you watch the show today.
I want you to think about.

1240
01:04:44.005 --> 01:04:45.089
what do you wanna be?

1241
01:04:45.172 --> 01:04:47.216
Do you wanna be
one of the dancers up here?

1242
01:04:47.300 --> 01:04:49.260
Do you wanna be one of the singers?

1243
01:04:49.343 --> 01:04:51.804
Do you wanna design the costumes?

1244
01:04:51.888 --> 01:04:53.806
Do you wanna do the makeup?

1245
01:04:53.890 --> 01:04:55.558
Do you wanna do the lighting?

1246
01:04:55.641 --> 01:04:57.643
There are many opportunities.

1247
01:04:57.727 --> 01:04:59.520
-Okay?
-[audience applauding]

1248
01:04:59.604 --> 01:05:04.025
All right.
so. I gotta go and get into character.

1249
01:05:04.108 --> 01:05:06.152
[in a mousy voice]
I gotta go! I gotta go! I gotta go!

1250
01:05:06.235 --> 01:05:08.738
I gotta go get--
get my character together.

1251
01:05:08.821 --> 01:05:10.948
I'm running. I'll see you later!

1252
01:05:11.032 --> 01:05:12.950
[audience cheering. applauding]

1253
01:05:15.828 --> 01:05:17.830
[audience applauding. whooping]

1254
01:05:28.507 --> 01:05:31.177
♪ Hang on the mistletoe ♪

1255
01:05:31.260 --> 01:05:35.222
♪ I'm gonna get to know you better ♪

1256
01:05:36.557 --> 01:05:38.476
-[adult male singer and kids]
♪ This Christmas ♪

1257
01:05:38.559 --> 01:05:41.562
[Nicholas] It's Christmas.
and everybody's having the big. fun party.

1258
01:05:41.646 --> 01:05:44.065
but then Frankie. Kara's brother.

1259
01:05:44.148 --> 01:05:47.318
he gets jealous that Kara
gets the Nutcracker instead of him.

1260
01:05:47.401 --> 01:05:50.529
So him and his friends
try to steal the Nutcracker from her.

1261
01:05:50.613 --> 01:05:52.907
but then the Nutcracker breaks.

1262
01:05:52.990 --> 01:05:56.077
So then. she gets sad. then magic happens.

1263
01:05:56.160 --> 01:05:58.496
and she's going
to all these different places.

1264
01:05:58.579 --> 01:06:00.122
[solemn music playing]

1265
01:06:02.208 --> 01:06:04.585
[Jalyn] I was just really nervous
before I went on.

1266
01:06:04.669 --> 01:06:07.588
and my mom was backstage.
helping me get ready.

1267
01:06:08.089 --> 01:06:11.384
And she was just telling me.
"Whatever happens. you can't change it.

1268
01:06:11.467 --> 01:06:14.553
but. as long as you do your best.
you know it's gonna be okay."

1269
01:06:14.637 --> 01:06:16.847
And that's what helped me
get through the show.

1270
01:06:22.019 --> 01:06:26.107
What makes me happiest about this place
is to watch their faces.

1271
01:06:26.190 --> 01:06:28.859
Some of them
that have never been in theater before

1272
01:06:28.943 --> 01:06:30.569
get standing ovations.

1273
01:06:31.278 --> 01:06:33.155
and to watch their faces. it's like…

1274
01:06:33.948 --> 01:06:34.865
it's unbelievable.

1275
01:06:34.949 --> 01:06:36.325
[epic music playing]

1276
01:06:39.745 --> 01:06:41.747
[Eartha] You wanna keep growing.

1277
01:06:41.831 --> 01:06:44.500
You never feel that you have arrived.
or you've made it.

1278
01:06:44.583 --> 01:06:46.210
or there's nothing else left.

1279
01:06:46.836 --> 01:06:50.756
Always keep growing.
Open yourself up to greater possibilities.

1280
01:06:50.840 --> 01:06:52.842
This is what they take away with them.

1281
01:06:53.843 --> 01:06:54.844
[music stops]

1282
01:06:54.927 --> 01:06:56.554
[audience applauding. whooping]

1283
01:06:58.139 --> 01:06:59.140
[applause fades]

1284
01:06:59.807 --> 01:07:01.809
[cicadas singing]

1285
01:07:01.892 --> 01:07:03.894
[mysterious music playing]

1286
01:07:11.152 --> 01:07:15.197
[Karen]
The process. from September to December.

1287
01:07:15.281 --> 01:07:16.741
it's pretty intense

1288
01:07:16.824 --> 01:07:19.410
Those students who participate.

1289
01:07:19.910 --> 01:07:23.622
I would say. grow tenfold.

1290
01:07:24.290 --> 01:07:25.958
in learning their craft.

1291
01:07:26.042 --> 01:07:28.294
in becoming a family.

1292
01:07:28.377 --> 01:07:32.798
being on stage in front of 1.800 people.

1293
01:07:32.882 --> 01:07:34.508
bearing their soul.

1294
01:07:34.592 --> 01:07:37.928
Children are not the same
once they do the Hot Chocolate Nutcracker.

1295
01:07:38.012 --> 01:07:39.847
They're brand-new.

1296
01:07:41.515 --> 01:07:44.977
[Chantel] Some of these kids had no idea
that they even want to dance.

1297
01:07:45.061 --> 01:07:48.939
but when they're introduced to it
and fall in love. it's something special.

1298
01:07:49.023 --> 01:07:53.903
And then some of them are off on Broadway.
doing things they never thought they could

1299
01:07:53.986 --> 01:07:56.822
and I think
that's what the arts does for people.

1300
01:07:56.906 --> 01:07:59.950
It can take you
wherever you want to be in the world.

1301
01:08:00.034 --> 01:08:01.285
[Bollywood music playing]

1302
01:08:07.416 --> 01:08:12.254
[Vivian] As a dancer.
it takes discipline and determination

1303
01:08:12.338 --> 01:08:16.342
and the willingness to continue.

1304
01:08:16.425 --> 01:08:19.386
no matter how many times you fall down.

1305
01:08:20.346 --> 01:08:21.847
[music stops]

1306
01:08:21.931 --> 01:08:25.476
Because success
is one step beyond failure.

1307
01:08:25.559 --> 01:08:26.977
[percussive music playing]

1308
01:08:39.949 --> 01:08:43.119
[Savoy]
My dream. dream. dream school is USC.

1309
01:08:43.202 --> 01:08:46.413
My audition is in. like. a couple weeks.

1310
01:08:46.497 --> 01:08:48.624
so I'm freaking out
a little bit. but. like.

1311
01:08:48.707 --> 01:08:52.253
it's cool-- I got a new leotard for it.
My mom bought me a new leotard. [laughs]

1312
01:09:04.473 --> 01:09:06.642
-[music stops]
-[audience applauds. whoops]

1313
01:09:06.725 --> 01:09:08.227
[rhythmic jazz music playing]

1314
01:09:13.899 --> 01:09:15.901
[JoAnn] One day.
I had a long talk with my friend.

1315
01:09:15.985 --> 01:09:18.154
and she told me. like.
"You need to teach."

1316
01:09:18.237 --> 01:09:21.574
I'm like. "Really? I didn't know."
She's like. "Yeah. that's your thing."

1317
01:09:21.657 --> 01:09:23.492
I taught my first class. and it was like.

1318
01:09:23.576 --> 01:09:27.663
"Wow. like. I do like to teach.
Maybe I should continue doing this."

1319
01:09:35.671 --> 01:09:38.007
[Chantel] The kids forget sometimes
when we're teaching them…

1320
01:09:38.090 --> 01:09:42.887
They think that. "Oh. they must be old."
and. "Oh. they don't do this anymore."

1321
01:09:42.970 --> 01:09:46.765
They don't get to see the-- the--
the professional side of what we still do.

1322
01:09:46.849 --> 01:09:49.393
So here I am. the teacher one day.

1323
01:09:49.476 --> 01:09:52.479
but in that audition.
with some of these major artists.

1324
01:09:52.563 --> 01:09:53.689
on tours.

1325
01:09:53.772 --> 01:09:57.526
I'm right there in the same playing field
as some of my students.

1326
01:09:58.360 --> 01:10:00.196
It's good. It's healthy competition.

1327
01:10:04.658 --> 01:10:08.370
[Giana] Some surprises happen
during the teaching years.

1328
01:10:08.454 --> 01:10:11.582
Some student
that doesn't look very promising.

1329
01:10:11.665 --> 01:10:15.044
through the hard work and open mind.

1330
01:10:15.127 --> 01:10:16.837
will jump up.

1331
01:10:18.380 --> 01:10:20.716
[percussive music playing]

1332
01:10:32.144 --> 01:10:33.687
[hip-hop music playing]

1333
01:10:55.542 --> 01:10:58.462
If I ever make my own dance studio.
I want it to be. like.

1334
01:10:58.545 --> 01:11:02.716
a dance studio where you can come
and pay how much you're able to pay.

1335
01:11:02.800 --> 01:11:06.553
There's a lot of good dancers out there.
and they just-- they're not in dance class

1336
01:11:06.637 --> 01:11:08.180
'cause they don't have enough money.

1337
01:11:08.264 --> 01:11:10.182
[scatting and percussion playing]

1338
01:11:23.112 --> 01:11:27.032
[Savion] They can take this information
and go on and be better dancers.

1339
01:11:27.116 --> 01:11:31.662
They can take this information and go on
to be better humans. humanitarians.

1340
01:11:31.745 --> 01:11:34.790
It's the learning. It's the teaching.
It's how they receive it.

1341
01:11:34.873 --> 01:11:37.835
I want them to just walk out different.

1342
01:11:37.918 --> 01:11:39.336
[classical music playing]

1343
01:11:43.257 --> 01:11:44.591
[Lauren] I love the way…

1344
01:11:46.176 --> 01:11:48.012
it felt to become music.

1345
01:11:48.846 --> 01:11:52.057
If you could physically think
of what it feels like to be music.

1346
01:11:52.725 --> 01:11:54.727
to physically become music.

1347
01:11:55.436 --> 01:11:56.937
that's what it's like dancing.

1348
01:11:57.604 --> 01:12:01.942
Like… to become the note
or the instrument or the beat.

1349
01:12:05.321 --> 01:12:08.198
-That's what it's like to dance.
-[applauding in distance]

1350
01:12:11.994 --> 01:12:13.746
[Kylie] By the end of my recovery period.

1351
01:12:13.829 --> 01:12:18.125
Miss Allen called to ask
if I wanted to do the Fairy Queen part.

1352
01:12:18.709 --> 01:12:24.590
And I was scared. I was so scared
because I knew that Miss Allen called.

1353
01:12:24.673 --> 01:12:30.179
that means I am gonna
have to get back to the real work.

1354
01:12:43.734 --> 01:12:48.113
It was hard. but doing Fairy Queen
made me wanna dance again.

1355
01:12:48.197 --> 01:12:50.407
Like. I got that… like. that fight back.

1356
01:12:51.241 --> 01:12:53.827
I don't know how. I don´t.
like. know what made it.

1357
01:12:53.911 --> 01:12:55.913
but maybe
because I had to overcome myself.

1358
01:13:02.461 --> 01:13:04.713
[April]
I think the biggest sacrifice is…

1359
01:13:04.797 --> 01:13:05.964
time.

1360
01:13:06.048 --> 01:13:09.635
You spend so much time
training and training and training.

1361
01:13:10.302 --> 01:13:12.179
You sometimes just have to sacrifice

1362
01:13:12.262 --> 01:13:15.557
the regular middle-school.
high-school life

1363
01:13:15.641 --> 01:13:17.768
so when you're 20-something.

1364
01:13:18.352 --> 01:13:19.770
you're phenomenal.

1365
01:13:23.649 --> 01:13:26.402
[Karen] There's something about dance…

1366
01:13:26.485 --> 01:13:29.905
When you know
you're leaving your first dancing school.

1367
01:13:29.988 --> 01:13:32.658
and you're getting ready
to go out into the world.

1368
01:13:33.325 --> 01:13:37.246
with that wealth of information
that you've been receiving

1369
01:13:37.329 --> 01:13:41.375
since you were five years old
or seven years old or eight years old

1370
01:13:41.458 --> 01:13:45.754
is no longer just in your head.
but it is in your body.

1371
01:13:45.838 --> 01:13:48.674
It's in the way you talk.
It's in the way you walk.

1372
01:13:50.175 --> 01:13:52.136
That's when you become a dancer.

1373
01:13:52.219 --> 01:13:56.807
When the essence of what it is
and the essence of who you are

1374
01:13:56.890 --> 01:13:58.934
come together as one.

1375
01:13:59.726 --> 01:14:02.354
that's when you become an artist.

1376
01:14:12.448 --> 01:14:14.408
[audience laughs softly]

1377
01:14:16.410 --> 01:14:18.579
[applauding gradually intensifies]

1378
01:14:19.997 --> 01:14:22.583
This is a lifelong proposition.

1379
01:14:24.334 --> 01:14:25.669
It's a marriage.

1380
01:14:26.253 --> 01:14:29.798
It is. and it's one that I want to see…

1381
01:14:31.175 --> 01:14:33.469
have a continuation.

1382
01:14:34.470 --> 01:14:39.099
So that even past my prime
or ability to do what I do.

1383
01:14:39.183 --> 01:14:40.809
it will keep going.

1384
01:14:42.019 --> 01:14:44.229
'Cause I'm always gonna be
one of those kids.

1385
01:14:44.771 --> 01:14:45.981
I don't care if I'm 90.

1386
01:14:46.064 --> 01:14:48.525
I'm always.
in my heart. one of those kids

1387
01:14:48.609 --> 01:14:50.360
looking for that opportunity.

1388
01:14:50.444 --> 01:14:52.446
looking for who's gonna train me.

1389
01:14:52.529 --> 01:14:55.657
how am I gonna get to be
who I really know I could be?

1390
01:14:55.741 --> 01:14:57.242
Where's my opportunity?

1391
01:14:57.951 --> 01:15:00.871
I'm always gonna be
one of those kids in my heart.

